type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

By default, typing in the palette filters the //current stage's// visible rows by substring match against each row's `name` and `hint`. Two pill strips widen this:

! Reach (where) — mutually exclusive

|!Pill |!Leader |!Walks |
|🔍 Here |`d` |Every reachable drill below the current stage |
|🌐 Everywhere |`g` |Every reachable drill from the active view's root |

Picking a Reach result replays the drill path so the cascade arrives at the row's natural parent.

! Search-in (what) — accumulating

|!Pill |!Leader |!Reads |
|🏷 Name |(individual) |Row's display name (default-on if no pills) |
|💡 Hint |(individual) |Row's subtitle |
|📝 Description |(individual) |`ca-description` — surfaces as snippet line |
|↪ Aliases |(individual) |`ca-aliases` — synonyms |
|🔎 Search-text |(individual) |`ca-search-text` — catch-all bag |
|📄 Text |(individual) |Tiddler `text` field — body |
|''(all 6 above)'' |`a` |Pushes every shipped Search-in pill at once |

Active Search-in pills //union// — the matcher reads the combined field set.

! Multi-match visualisation

A row that matches in multiple fields gets:

* ''Inline highlight'' on its name / hint (whichever matched).
* ''One snippet line per non-displayed match'' — beneath the row, prefixed by the matched field name + context window around the hit.

! Picking a deep result — three gestures

When Reach is active, results carry a drill path. Three keys distinguish what happens after the path replays:

|!Gesture |!Effect |
|`↵` Enter |Replay path + fire (drill into drills, execute leaves) |
|`→` Right |Replay path + drill only (no-op on plain leaves) |
|`Space` |''Pin only'' — replay path, select row, do NOT fire. Safe for destructive matches. |

''→'' Full deep-search docs: <$link to="$:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/doc/deep-search">doc/deep-search</$link>
